Noun
Common Noun - Common names for person, place, animal or thing - girl, boy, school, chocolate
Proper Noun - Specific name used for a person, place, animal or thing. - Anuj, Mumbai, Cadbury, Sujata
Collective Noun - Special name for a group of people, animals, and things. - herd, family, bunch, library
Gender Noun - Common nouns to show male or female - girl, father, woman, son
Countable Noun - Common nouns that can counted - pencil, book, box, bus
Uncountable Noun - Common nouns that cannot be counted - sugar, water, rain, milk

