Adverbs:
An adverb describes the action (verb). There are different types of adverbs.

Adverb of Manner - how? He played quite wisely.
Adverb of Time - When? She is coming here tomorrow.
Adverb of Place - Where? I looked for his everywhere.
Adverb of frequency - How often? She is never on time.
Adverb of Degree - How much? I have almost completed this.
Adverb of Reason - Why? I will not go because I am ill

