Modals

Modals tell us something about the very without the action taking place. The 4 modals we learnt were 'can', 'may', 'must for necessity', and 'must for obligation'

an ability, a possibility, a necessity, an obligation

I can read easily.
I may swim tomorrow.
I must drink enough water.
You must keep your promise.

Prepositions:
Prepositions are short words that connect different parts of a sentence. They tell us the relationship between people, place and things.

on - used to show day/date, used to show position of a person/Object
at - shows exact time
in - show part of the day
towards - shows direction
near - shows position
during - show duration/time
for - shows reason/purpose
with - shows means/possession
without - shows lack of possession
against - to disagree with something

