Rules for the sound of letter 'y'

The sound of the letter 'y' changes as per the change in its position and where it comes in a word.

Position - example - rule

'y' at the beginning of the word - yellow - It makes the /y/ sound.
'y' at the end of the word - cry - It makes the long /i/ sound.
'y' comes after a vowel - key - it remains silent.
'y' comes in the middle of the word - symbol - It makes the short /i/ sound




